myEP is a digital European Parliament observer tool offering you a quick and easy access to key information about European Parliament activities, documents and members.

What can you do with the myEP app?
* Browse upcoming, recently added or past European Parliament committee and plenary meetings;
* Check committee or plenary agenda in an user-friendly and accessible form; 
* Quickly access documents relevant to specific agenda items;
* Review plenary overall, aggregated and individual roll call vote results;
* Web-stream committee and plenary meetings;
* Browse recently added documents and publications;
* Quickly change the language of the selected document;
* Browse the list of MEPs and filter them by their country, political group and their name;
* Check the list of MEPs working at the selected committee;
* Get details of the specific MEP, including their email addresses and office phone numbers;
* Share agendas and documents with your colleagues;
* Receive notifications with key news stories;
* Optionally, browse key meetings at the Council of the European Union.

myEP app includes publicly available data from the Council of the European Union and European Parliament.

myEP app is not affiliated, associated, authorised, endorsed by or in any way officially connected with the European Parliament, Council of the European Union or any other public and/or private entity.

myQuran application is your universal assistant, which allows you to benefit from reading and listening to the Quran. myQuran will always be at your fingertips, wherever you are.

Features:

— Translation into 25 languages;
— Tafsir - interpretation of the Quran;
— Original Quran text with tajweed rules;
— Detailed information for each surah;
— Screen with Ajza;
— Easy to use and functional audio player;
— Ability to play each ayah separately (for 11 recitors);
— Interactive surah and ayah search; 
— Ability to add ayahs to favourites;
— Bookmarks;
— Custom font and font sizes;
— Quick access toolbar on the main screen;
— Ability to delete cached audio files;
— Customizable notifications;
— 3D touch support;

Please keep in mind, that you can share ayahs using e-mail, SMS, Facebook, Twitter, WhatsApp, Telegram, VK and other social networks. 

The application allows you to listen to Quran recitation with the voices of the best reciters in the world. Such as: Abdul Baset Abdus Samad; Abdul Rahman al-Sudais; Abdullah Awad al-Juhani; Abdullah Ibn Ali Basfar; Abu Bakr ash-Shatri; Ahmad bin Ali al-Ajmi; Emad al-Mansary; Hani ar-Rifai; Maher al-Muaiqly; Mahmood al-Rifai; Mahmoud Khalil al-Hussary; Mishari Rashid al-Afasy; Muhammad al-Luhaidan; Muhammad al-Minshawi; Nasser al-Qatami; Saad al-Ghamdi; Salah Abdul Rahman Bukhatir; Salah al-Budair; Salah al-Hashim; Saud al-Shuraim; Tawfeeq al-Sayegh; Yasser al-Dosari.

